			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2020</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Search-Based and Fault-Tolerant Approach to Concurrent Model Synchronisation</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/NilsBWeidmann.html">Nils B. Weidmann</a>, <a href="../profile/LarsFritsche.html">Lars Fritsche</a>, <a href="../profile/AnthonyAnjorin.html">Anthony Anjorin</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3426425.3426932">10.1145/3426425.3426932</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagM">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s central topic is specifying or applying transformations (rewriting/mapping/synchronization).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It performs mapping/conversion/synchronization between representations (horizontal transformations).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> It targets usability (developer interaction, comprehension, editing experience).
</li></ul></li></ul>
